<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="1224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1224">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/341</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-29T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>643. See Department’s 613, January 13, 6 p.m., and telegraph result your
                            representations. If authorities have not yet answered, renew request to
                            be promptly informed of action taken. Mining companies anxiously
                            awaiting information.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
